tee has a simple main loop:
while not EOF:
  (synchrounously) read up to BUFSIZE bytes from stdin into buf
  for each output file:
    (synchrounously) write buf to file<p>(source code here: <a href="http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/coreutils.git/tree/src/tee.c" rel="nofollow">http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/coreutils.git/tree/src/tee....</a>)<p>All of the reads and writes are done through synchronous file apis. I don't see where you are getting one-thread-per-file (or any other kind of parallelism) there.
